# 3. FutureгЃ«FeatureпјЃ

iHaz Producer: So, we'd like for you to all appear on iHaz as part of our вЂњFeature the FutureвЂќ mini segment...
Shizuku: Feature the Future...?
Airi: Based on its name, I assume it's the segment dedicated to introducing up-and-coming idols.
iHaz Producer: Yes, that's right. We have idols who are currently trending to appear as guests and ask them about their personal lives.
iHaz Producer: And the one asking the questions will be, well... Cheerful * Days.
Shizuku: Yes, we heard...
iHaz Producer: Here's the script for that day. It includes a list of questions that you can expect to be asked, so please try to have your responses ready by then.
Haruka: Understood.
Minori: What...? Those questions are already in the script?! I was under the impression that everyone thought of those on the spot...!
iHaz Producer: Haha. I understand why you're surprised since some shows in fact don't have scripts... However, in general, we ask people to prepare their responses in advance.
iHaz Producer: By doing so, shoots go much more smoothly and our idols can talk freely without feeling too pressed.
Minori: W-Wow! I had no idea...!
Minori: I mean, I was always amazed by how everyone had all these interesting stories to tell. Now it all makes sense...
Airi: Hehe. I used to feel the same way about variety shows way back when.
Haruka: We're all pretty used to this now, but I was just as surprised in the beginning, Minori.
iHaz Producer: However, please keep in mind that these questions are the ones you can вЂњexpectвЂќ to hear.
iHaz Producer: iHaz has earned its reputation for featuring raw and uncut conversations between idols. Surprise stories are always welcome.
iHaz Producer: So we're actually looking forward to seeing how you and the MCs interact.
Shizuku: Come to think of it, these sorts of segments don't always end up following the script...
Airi: Yeah. We should be ready to answer any questions that are thrown our way.
Minori: Then, we really do need to practice!
iHaz Producer: Hahaha. There's no need to feel so alarmed. You'll be talking to girls around the same age as you, so as long as we get to see you all having a fun conversation, our viewers will...
Shizuku: Hm? Someone's at the door.
iHaz Producer: That must be our staff. Would you mind giving me a minute...?
Airi: Yes, of course.
iHaz Producer: Sorry for the interruption. There's plenty of snacks to go around, so please feel free to have more.
Minori: The producer seems like a really busy person...
Shizuku: Yes, and he's apparently in charge of a few other programs... Despite that, he took the time to meet with us.
Airi: I thought so when I read his email, but he seems like a really nice person. It's also reassuring that he's great at explaining things.
Haruka: Me too. If our actual appearance also goes this well...
iHaz Producer: Excuse me, MORE MORE JUMP! Do you have a minute?
Haruka: Yes, of course... How can we help you?
iHaz Producer: So, they're shooting a variety show called вЂњPrincess's BrunchвЂќ in the studio just above us. They're taking a break right now and some folks from there came to say hello to us...
iHaz Producer: They're the MCs for the next iHaz... Cheerful * Days.
Haruka: ...!
iHaz Producer: Then, when we mentioned that MORE MORE JUMP! is here to meet with us, they said that they'd also like to say hi to all of you.
Shizuku: Say hi to us...?
Airi: Shizuku...
iHaz Producer: I'm aware that there's some history between you and Cheerful * Days, Hinomori. We heard some rumors through the grapevine not too long ago...
iHaz Producer: Which is why we were worried that you wouldn't accept our offer to appear on this program.
Minori: What...?
iHaz Producer: And yet, you accepted. Which tells me that you've prepared yourselves for this.
Shizuku: ...
iHaz Producer: Even if you don't speak with them today, you will when we shoot. So...
iHaz Producer: If possible, I'd like for you to all meet now instead of later. What do you say?
Minori: Um...
Shizuku: I agree...
Shizuku: I was actually hoping to see them as well, so if you don't mind...
Minori: Shizuku...
Shizuku: Is that okay with all of you...?
Minori: Oh, um... Y-Yeah...
Airi: Okay...
iHaz Producer: Then, I don't want to pull them away from the studio, so let's go to them.
iHaz Producer: They should be back upstairs now, so I'll show you all the way.
Shizuku: Wonderful. Thank you very much.
Equipment Tech: How's this? Is it good where it is?
Sound Tech: Can someone fix that lapel mic?
Minori: Wow! This studio's so big...! With a staff to match...!
Airi: Now that you mention it, we don't exactly belong here. Are we really allowed to enter?
iHaz Producer: I've already asked and received permission to show you around. Now, where did Cheerful * Days go...
???: Oh, hello. Are you here to see us?
Shizuku: Oh...
???: We know you're very busy, so the others and I decided to wait until later to speak with you again... Thank you very much for taking the time out of your schedule to do this.
Shizuku: (Arisa...)
Shizuku: ...
iHaz Producer: Ah, hello. I'd rather not force you to make the same trip twice. Especially since we asked you to sub in as the MCs on such short notice...
Group Members: Please, don't mind us! We're really happy about getting to appear on iHaz! We've been wanting to for a while now!
Arisa: Yes, we have. Also...
Arisa: We get to see a familiar face.
Shizuku: Yes... It's nice to see all of you again. I'm glad to see that you're all doing well.
Group Members: Likewise, Shizuku. We watched some of your streams. You seem to be having way more fun than when you were with Cheerful * Days.
Shizuku: Um, well...
Arisa: We can discuss that another time. For now, we're simply here to greet each other.
Arisa: We're meeting as two different groups today, but I'm looking forward to appearing alongside all of you.
Arisa: I know a lot happened between us...
Arisa: But iHaz is pretty well known throughout the idol-fan community and has a very passionate staff onboard. So, I want to make the most of this opportunity.
Arisa: So, Shizuku... As short as the MORE MORE JUMP! segment is going to be, I want to do it right.
Arisa: I'm going to give it everything I have, so I hope you will as well.
Minori: Oh! U-Uhh...
Shizuku: Yes, we will. We may be a bit rough around the edges since it's going to be our first appearance on TV as MORE MORE JUMP!
Shizuku: But we also plan to give it everything we have. We'll be looking forward to the conversation we're going to have during our shoot.
Arisa: *Nod*
Arisa: Then, for now, thank you all very much. We'll see you again during the actual shoot.
Arisa: You as well, sir. See you then. Now, if you'll excuse us.
Minori: Whoa...! That... That really made my hairs stand up!
Airi: You can tell something fierce is hiding behind that smile of hers.
Airi: However, she was probably telling the truth...
Haruka: I agree. She seems to genuinely want the show to go well.
Haruka: Which makes sense since she's in a group that's maintained its popularity for so long...
Airi: Which means we can't let our guard down. Let's prepare as much as we can leading up to the shoot.
Haruka & Minori: Yeah...!
Shizuku: (The others seem determined to make sure our shoot goes well.)
Shizuku: (That means I also need to do what I can...)
